"id\": \"migrated-20\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"Risk: regex-based validation may produce false positives for complex Dockerfiles\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-21\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"`patches/infra/` directory doesn't exist yet — first file created there\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-22\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**Branch coverage at 87.5%** — The `line !== undefined` conditional in `dfGap()` helper has one branch not fully covered. Cosmetic; both paths exercised indirectly.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-23\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**Verification tools check has potential false positives** — Regex checks for tool names anywhere in apt-get/apk lines. Matches story's stated approach: \\\"False positives are acceptable.\\\"\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-24\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-25\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity** in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains. Fixed.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-26\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**MEDIUM: Redundant double-read** of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`. Fixed.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-27\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns** — regex updated. Fixed.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-28\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern** — test added. Fixed.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-29\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**LOW (not fixed): `checkVerificationTools` loose matching** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file. Acceptable per story design.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-30\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**LOW (not fixed): `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number** — inconsistent with other checks but not a bug.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-31\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**Coverage: 96.99% overall, 2817 tests, all 120 files above 80% floor**\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-32\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"9/10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-33\",\n      \"story\": \"4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation\",\n      \"description\": \"**AC10 FAIL:** `validateDockerfile()` warnings stored in `DockerfileValidationResult.warnings[]` but not propagated by `checkInfrastructure()` to audit output. Fixed by adding warning-to-gap propagation in dimensions.ts. Test added (2820 tests pass). Story returned to `verifying` for re-verification in next session.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-34\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"Expanded from 3 epic ACs to 10 for full implementation coverage\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-35\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"Risk: AC #5 (generated Dockerfile passes validateDockerfile) depends on template content matching all 6 rule categories — tight coupling with Story 4.1's validator regex\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-36\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"AC #3 (generic template) — existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` uses `COPY . /workspace/` which would fail \\\"no source copy\\\" rule. Generated templates must differ.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-37\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"Init orchestrator (`init-project.ts`) is already complex; template generation delegated to new `dockerfile-template.ts` to minimize changes\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-38\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"**Workaround:** Templates use single-line `apt-get install curl jq` instead of multi-line format. `validateDockerfile()` checks lines independently, so multi-line `\\\\` continuations cause false negatives. Templates deviate from story spec format but satisfy functional requirement (AC #5).\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-39\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"**Task 5.2 skipped:** No new init-project integration tests added — init-project.ts has heavy mocking; template function fully tested via its own 22-test file.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-40\",\n      \"story\": \"4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\",\n      \"description\": \"**Code quality concern:** `checkVerificationTools()` in dockerfile-validator.ts only checks single lines, not multi-line RUN instructions. Validator and template generator coupled to single-line format.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","numLines":467,"startLine":1,"totalLines":467}}}
