 that missing log statements are caught before verification.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md:350:1. **Given** `patches/review/review-enforcement.md` is updated, **When** code review runs, **Then** it includes: \"Run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` and report gaps.\"\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-codeharness-arch-overhaul-2026-03-17.md:34:2. **No clear ownership.** init.ts does stack detection, dependency management, Docker setup, BMAD installation, documentation scaffolding, state management, and OTLP configuration. harness-run.md is a 500-line markdown file that does sprint management, story selection, dev orchestration, code review, verification, retry tracking, and retrospectives. When something breaks, there's no obvious place to fix it.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-codeharness-arch-overhaul-2026-03-17.md:67:| **Reviewer** | `review/` | Code review orchestration, quality gates | Part of harness-run.md |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:400:- Configurable minimum file threshold (default 3, NFR27)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:767:│   │   ├── pre-commit-gate.sh          # FR26-FR27: Block commit without quality gates\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:768:│   │   ├── post-write-check.sh         # FR28: Prompt OTLP verification\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:847:| Enforcement (FR26-FR31) | `src/commands/state.ts` | `hooks/*.sh` |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md:50:| **Static analysis** | Log statements in error handlers, key functions have entry/exit logging, log levels are appropriate | During code review, as part of audit |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md:91:**Observability-aware development:** During story development, the agent adds appropriate logging. During code review, static analysis flags missing log statements. During verification, runtime validation checks telemetry flows. Observability is enforced like test coverage — not a separate concern.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md:99:- **Static analysis catches missing logs during code review.** Before code ships, not after deployment.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md:116:6. **Observability enforcement in dev/review workflows** — static analysis runs during code review. Missing log statements flagged as review issues. Patches updated with observability requirements.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:42:- **BMAD distribution with harness built in:** codeharness installs BMAD, patches all workflows (story, dev, code review, retro), bridges stories to Ralph tasks, and runs the autonomous loop. One tool, not two.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:217:- **claude-code-harness** — Code review loops only. No real-world verification.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:218:- **ralphex** — Multi-agent code review. No verification or observability.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:329:| BMAD patches | CLI lib | Apply harness patches to story template, dev workflow, code review, retro. Idempotent. Sprint planning patch integrates `bd ready` for backlog. |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:432:- FR26: System can enforce per-commit quality gates (tests pass, coverage met) via PreToolUse hook\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:433:- FR27: System can block git commits without prior quality gate pass\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:434:- FR28: System can inject verification prompts after code changes via PostToolUse hook\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:556:- NFR26: Generated documentation (`docs/generated/`, `docs/quality/`) must have \"DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY\" headers\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:557:- NFR27: Module detection threshold must be configurable (default: 3 files mini