{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JbR61nDEGqyffRBSGgmWxd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## WHY\n     2→\n     3→Dev agents repeatedly shipped code without reading module conventions (AGENTS.md),\n     4→skipped observability checks, and produced features that could not be verified\n     5→from outside the source tree. This patch enforces architecture awareness,\n     6→observability validation, documentation hygiene, test coverage gates, and\n     7→black-box thinking — all operational failures observed in prior sprints.\n     8→(FR33, FR34, NFR20)\n     9→\n    10→## Codeharness Development Enforcement\n    11→\n    12→### Architecture Awareness\n    13→\n    14→Before writing code, read the relevant `AGENTS.md` file for the module being changed. Understand:\n    15→- Build commands and test runners\n    16→- Module boundaries and conventions\n    17→- What NOT to do (common pitfalls documented from prior incidents)\n    18→\n    19→### Observability\n    20→\n    21→After running tests, verify telemetry is flowing:\n    22→- Query VictoriaLogs to confirm log events from test runs\n    23→- If observability is configured, traces should be visible for CLI operations\n    24→\n    25→### Documentation\n    26→\n    27→- Update `AGENTS.md` for all changed modules\n    28→- Keep exec-plan current with implementation state\n    29→\n    30→### Testing\n    31→\n    32→- All tests pass before moving to review\n    33→- Coverage gate: 100% of new/changed code\n    34→- Run `npm test` / `pytest` and verify no regressions\n    35→\n    36→### Black-Box Thinking\n    37→\n    38→Write code that can be verified from the outside. Ask yourself:\n    39→- Can a user exercise this feature from the CLI alone?\n    40→- Is the behavior documented in README.md?\n    41→- Would a verifier with NO source access be able to tell if this works?\n    42→\n    43→If the answer is \"no\", the feature has a testability gap — fix the CLI/docs, not the verification process.\n    44→\n    45→### Dockerfile Maintenance\n    46→\n    47→If this story adds a new runtime dependency, check whether the Dockerfile needs updating:\n    48→- New system package required at runtime (e.g., `libssl`, `ffmpeg`) — add to `apt-get install` line\n    49→- New binary expected on PATH — add install step to Dockerfile\n    50→- New Python package needed — add to `pip install` or `requirements.txt` COPY\n    51→- Verify the updated Dockerfile still passes `validateDockerfile()` with zero gaps\n    52→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BXi4AhmTJeJqqZtqWChyrJ","session_id":"7be24b04-34e1-424a-85e4-e656cce56dfe","uuid":"923b780f-f6fd-4de8-9823-feee583eab0f","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:07:22.015Z"}
