{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0116hY2Yg83WPjhT2bPfKgDf","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7be24b04-34e1-424a-85e4-e656cce56dfe","uuid":"ea6e0934-6b54-485a-ba53-bca13a1683c9","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:09:30.006Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Showboat not installed — skipping re-verification (warning only, not blocking)\n\n","newString":"- Showboat not installed — skipping re-verification (warning only, not blocking)\n\n### 5-1-code-review-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-21T06:08Z)\n\n- **Workaround:** Sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent (per instructions) — manually reconciled after.\n- **Lightweight story:** Primarily patch-file updates with minimal TypeScript code. Main work is markdown content in enforcement patches.\n- **Risk:** AC #2 and #3 depend on LLM agent behavior during real review sessions — unit tests can only verify patch content exists, not agent interpretation.\n- **Observation:** Epic ACs reference `patches/review/review-enforcement.md` but actual file is `patches/review/enforcement.md`.\n\n","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n---\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — create-story (2026-03-21T04:24Z)\n\n- **Previous sprint file collision:** An existing `3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge-command.md` exists from a previous sprint's Epic 3. No conflict since new file uses `3-3-onboard-alias.md`.\n- **Ambiguous AC3:** Epic says `codeharness onboard scan` should map to \"equivalent audit subcommand,\" but audit has no subcommands. Interpreted as deprecation warning + base audit run.\n- **Risk: Old exports removal.** `onboard.ts` exports `getLastScanResult()`, `getLastCoverageResult()`, `getLastAuditResult()`, and `resetLastScanResult()`. Need to verify no external consumers before removing.\n- **Risk: `onboard epic` subcommand has no audit equivalent.** Dropping silently may surprise users.\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — dev-story (2026-03-21T04:31Z)\n\n- **audit-action.ts branch coverage 95.83%:** Two uncovered branches (lines 96, 101) in JSON fix output formatting. Covered by audit.test.ts but not onboard.test.ts — redundant since both delegate to same handler.\n- **Test file size:** onboard.test.ts is 325 lines vs estimated 100-150. Consistent with project norms (audit.test.ts is 407 lines).\n- **console.log in shared handler:** audit-action.ts line 107 uses console.log directly. Story says \"Do NOT use console.log directly\" but formatAuditHuman() returns pre-formatted strings — wrapping in ok()/info() would double-prefix.\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — code-review (2026-03-21T04:38Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion** in audit-action.ts:86 — `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` bypassed type safety. Fixed with spread operator.\n- **MEDIUM: Dead branch guard** in audit-action.ts:101 — `fixStories &&` always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n- **MEDIUM: NFR9 violation** — onboard.test.ts at 325 lines, compacted to 230.\n- **MEDIUM: Branch coverage gap** — missing test for `skipped: true` path. Added, now 100%.\n- **LOW (not fixed): console.log in audit-action.ts:111** — established codebase pattern, needs new `raw()` output utility to fix properly.\n- **LOW (not fixed): formatAuditJson() is pass-through no-op** — exists for symmetry only.\n- **Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 119 files above 80% floor, 2783 tests pass**\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — verify (2026-03-21T05:10Z)\n\n- All 8 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n- Observability gaps: no structured log events emitted for any audit/onboard CLI interaction\n- Pre-existing test failure in run-helpers.test.ts (--live flag test) had to be fixed before verification could proceed — not related to this story\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — create-story (2026-03-21T05:14Z)\n\n- Ambiguity: rules markdown as code vs documentation — chose hardcoded rules with markdown as reference docs\n- Expanded ACs from 4 (epic) to 10 to cover each rule category individually\n- Risk: regex-based validation may produce false positives for complex Dockerfiles\n- `patches/infra/` directory doesn't exist yet — first file created there\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — dev-story (2026-03-21T05:22Z)\n\n- **Branch coverage at 87.5%** — The `line !== undefined` conditional in `dfGap()` helper has one branch not fully covered. Cosmetic; both paths exercised indirectly.\n- **Verification tools check has potential false positives** — Regex checks for tool names anywhere in apt-get/apk lines. Matches story's stated approach: \"False positives are acceptable.\"\n- **Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — code-review (2026-03-21T05:32Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity** in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: Redundant double-read** of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns** — regex updated. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern** — test added. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `checkVerificationTools` loose matching** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file. Acceptable per story design.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number** — inconsistent with other checks but not a bug.\n- **Coverage: 96.99% overall, 2817 tests, all 120 files above 80% floor**\n\n### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — verify (2026-03-21T05:35Z)\n\n- 9/10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n- **AC10 FAIL:** `validateDockerfile()` warnings stored in `DockerfileValidationResult.warnings[]` but not propagated by `checkInfrastructure()` to audit output. Fixed by adding warning-to-gap propagation in dimensions.ts. Test added (2820 tests pass). Story returned to `verifying` for re-verification in next session.\n\n### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — create-story (2026-03-21T05:42Z)\n\n- Expanded from 3 epic ACs to 10 for full implementation coverage\n- Risk: AC #5 (generated Dockerfile passes validateDockerfile) depends on template content matching all 6 rule categories — tight coupling with Story 4.1's validator regex\n- AC #3 (generic template) — existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` uses `COPY . /workspace/` which would fail \"no source copy\" rule. Generated templates must differ.\n- Init orchestrator (`init-project.ts`) is already complex; template generation delegated to new `dockerfile-template.ts` to minimize changes\n\n### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — dev-story (2026-03-21T05:45Z)\n\n- **Workaround:** Templates use single-line `apt-get install curl jq` instead of multi-line format. `validateDockerfile()` checks lines independently, so multi-line `\\` continuations cause false negatives. Templates deviate from story spec format but satisfy functional requirement (AC #5).\n- **Task 5.2 skipped:** No new init-project integration tests added — init-project.ts has heavy mocking; template function fully tested via its own 22-test file.\n- **Code quality concern:** `checkVerificationTools()` in dockerfile-validator.ts only checks single lines, not multi-line RUN instructions. Validator and template generator coupled to single-line format.\n\n### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — code-review (2026-03-21T05:54Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Unhandled writeFileSync exception** — violates Result<T> \"never throws\" contract. Fixed with try/catch.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing projectDir validation** — falsy values produce garbage paths. Fixed with guard clause.\n- **MEDIUM: Test mock leak** — `vi.clearAllMocks()` doesn't reset implementations, causing pollution. Fixed with `vi.resetAllMocks()`.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Redundant `resolvedStack` variable** — clear enough, no change needed.\n- **Coverage gap:** init-project.test.ts does not assert on `dockerfile` field in InitResult (tests predate story 4.2).\n- **Coverage: 96.98% overall, 2845 tests, all 121 files above 80% floor**\n\n### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — verify (2026-03-21T06:01Z)\n\n- All 10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n- No escalations, no failures\n- Showboat not installed — skipping re-verification (warning only, not blocking)\n\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":87,"oldLines":3,"newStart":87,"newLines":10,"lines":[" - No escalations, no failures"," - Showboat not installed — skipping re-verification (warning only, not blocking)"," ","+### 5-1-code-review-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-21T06:08Z)","+","+- **Workaround:** Sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent (per instructions) — manually reconciled after.","+- **Lightweight story:** Primarily patch-file updates with minimal TypeScript code. Main work is markdown content in enforcement patches.","+- **Risk:** AC #2 and #3 depend on LLM agent behavior during real review sessions — unit tests can only verify patch content exists, not agent interpretation.","+- **Observation:** Epic ACs reference `patches/review/review-enforcement.md` but actual file is `patches/review/enforcement.md`.","+"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
