{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018xZChMVojAsfis2Hpe9EUL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## WHY\n     2→\n     3→Review agents approved stories without verifying proof documents existed or\n     4→checking that evidence was black-box (not source-grep). Stories passed review\n     5→with fabricated output and missing coverage data. This patch enforces proof\n     6→existence, black-box evidence quality, and coverage delta reporting as hard\n     7→gates before a story can leave review.\n     8→(FR33, FR34, NFR20)\n     9→\n    10→## Codeharness Review Gates\n    11→\n    12→### Verification Proof\n    13→\n    14→- Proof document exists at `verification/<story-key>-proof.md`\n    15→- Proof passes `codeharness verify --story <id>` (parser checks for FAIL/ESCALATE verdicts)\n    16→- Every AC has functional evidence — reading docs alone is not evidence\n    17→- No fabricated output — all evidence must be from actual command execution\n    18→\n    19→### Proof Quality Checks\n    20→\n    21→The proof must pass black-box enforcement:\n    22→- Commands run via `docker exec` (not direct host access)\n    23→- Less than 50% of evidence commands are `grep` against `src/`\n    24→- Each AC section has at least one `docker exec`, `docker ps/logs`, or observability query\n    25→- `[FAIL]` verdicts outside code blocks cause the proof to fail\n    26→- `[ESCALATE]` is acceptable only when all automated approaches are exhausted\n    27→\n    28→### Code Quality\n    29→\n    30→- Coverage delta reported (before vs after)\n    31→- No coverage regression in changed files\n    32→- AGENTS.md is current for all changed modules\n    33→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NPoMRLksRrYS1379XfDBqY","session_id":"7be24b04-34e1-424a-85e4-e656cce56dfe","uuid":"7c702d28-7f18-4f4e-a9fc-0214ff46ff3a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:09:58.217Z"}
