{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SYFmth4jmfGkWhMfu7ffMP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Summary:**\n\n**Story:** 5-1-code-review-observability-check\n**Status:** verifying\n**Issues Found:** 0 High (fixed), 1 Medium (fixed), downgraded issues to LOW\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **[MEDIUM, fixed] Missing `--json` flag in review patch Semgrep command** -- `patches/review/enforcement.md` told the review agent to run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` but AC #6 requires JSON output (`--json`). The patch referenced \"Semgrep JSON output fields to extract\" but the command would produce human-readable output. Added `--json` flag. Updated corresponding test.\n\n2. **[MEDIUM, fixed] Tautological Semgrep JSON contract test** -- The original test created a mock object inline then asserted the properties it just defined exist. This can never fail. Replaced with a test that routes mock Semgrep JSON through the real `parseSemgrepOutput()` function from `analyzer.ts`, validating the actual contract between raw Semgrep output and the parsed `ObservabilityGap[]` shape. Added empty-results edge case test.\n\n3. **[MEDIUM, fixed] File reads at module scope** -- `readFileSync` calls were at module scope, meaning a missing patch file would crash all tests at import time. Moved to `beforeAll` for proper test isolation.\n\n**Results after fixes:**\n- Build: passes\n- Tests: 2855 pass (111 files), 0 failures, +2 new tests\n- Coverage: 96.98% overall (target 90%), all 121 files above 80% per-file floor\n- NFR9: all files under 300 lines\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- MEDIUM: Review patch missing `--json` flag in Semgrep command -- would produce wrong output format (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Tautological test -- Semgrep JSON contract test validated hardcoded mock against itself, could never fail (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Module-scope `readFileSync` -- test file crashes entirely if patch file missing (FIXED)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- LOW: Em dash vs double dash inconsistency -- `patches/review/enforcement.md` uses `\"static analysis skipped — install semgrep\"` (em dash) while `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts:72` uses `\"static analysis skipped -- install semgrep\"` (double dash). These are separate codepaths (patch is read by LLM agents, analyzer is programmatic), but the inconsistency could confuse downstream consumers. Pre-existing tech debt, not introduced by this story.\n- LOW: `ROOT` path resolution in test (line 6) uses fragile `__dirname` + four `..` segments. If directory structure changes, this breaks silently. A shared test utility for resolving project root would be more robust.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All files above 80% per-file floor. Overall at 96.98%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The story correctly treats patches as first-class artifacts read by LLM agents at review time. No unnecessary coupling to the programmatic `analyze()` path.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in-place."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acfaf323643453d77 (use SendMessage with to: 'acfaf323643453d77' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51179\ntool_uses: 43\nduration_ms: 208211</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7be24b04-34e1-424a-85e4-e656cce56dfe","uuid":"98a9625e-0e33-42f7-920e-30eedaa78650","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:15:56.469Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-1-code-review-observability-check.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"acfaf323643453d77","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Summary:**\n\n**Story:** 5-1-code-review-observability-check\n**Status:** verifying\n**Issues Found:** 0 High (fixed), 1 Medium (fixed), downgraded issues to LOW\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **[MEDIUM, fixed] Missing `--json` flag in review patch Semgrep command** -- `patches/review/enforcement.md` told the review agent to run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` but AC #6 requires JSON output (`--json`). The patch referenced \"Semgrep JSON output fields to extract\" but the command would produce human-readable output. Added `--json` flag. Updated corresponding test.\n\n2. **[MEDIUM, fixed] Tautological Semgrep JSON contract test** -- The original test created a mock object inline then asserted the properties it just defined exist. This can never fail. Replaced with a test that routes mock Semgrep JSON through the real `parseSemgrepOutput()` function from `analyzer.ts`, validating the actual contract between raw Semgrep output and the parsed `ObservabilityGap[]` shape. Added empty-results edge case test.\n\n3. **[MEDIUM, fixed] File reads at module scope** -- `readFileSync` calls were at module scope, meaning a missing patch file would crash all tests at import time. Moved to `beforeAll` for proper test isolation.\n\n**Results after fixes:**\n- Build: passes\n- Tests: 2855 pass (111 files), 0 failures, +2 new tests\n- Coverage: 96.98% overall (target 90%), all 121 files above 80% per-file floor\n- NFR9: all files under 300 lines\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- MEDIUM: Review patch missing `--json` flag in Semgrep command -- would produce wrong output format (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Tautological test -- Semgrep JSON contract test validated hardcoded mock against itself, could never fail (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Module-scope `readFileSync` -- test file crashes entirely if patch file missing (FIXED)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- LOW: Em dash vs double dash inconsistency -- `patches/review/enforcement.md` uses `\"static analysis skipped — install semgrep\"` (em dash) while `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts:72` uses `\"static analysis skipped -- install semgrep\"` (double dash). These are separate codepaths (patch is read by LLM agents, analyzer is programmatic), but the inconsistency could confuse downstream consumers. Pre-existing tech debt, not introduced by this story.\n- LOW: `ROOT` path resolution in test (line 6) uses fragile `__dirname` + four `..` segments. If directory structure changes, this breaks silently. A shared test utility for resolving project root would be more robust.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All files above 80% per-file floor. Overall at 96.98%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The story correctly treats patches as first-class artifacts read by LLM agents at review time. No unnecessary coupling to the programmatic `analyze()` path.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in-place."}],"totalDurationMs":208211,"totalTokens":51179,"totalToolUseCount":43,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1947,"cache_read_input_tokens":48440,"output_tokens":791,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_